^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|This is a good illustration of an important bidding principle. New suits by responder are forcing so Boater's 1D bid is forcing. But simple new suits by opener are not forcing. Some players get confused and think 1H here is forcing. It is not, because TJ is the opening bidder. It is fairly rare that Boater passes, but it is not forcing. If TJ wants to force, she has to jump shift to 2H (obviously not on this hand).|
